rstmals in Szene gesetzte Affenmensch.Die interdisziplinären Beiträge in diesem Band orientieren sich an der seither in zahllosen Variationen repräsentierten Figur. Sie streben eine kritische Auseinandersetzung mit den Diskursen um und den Bildern von Menschenaffen und Affenmenschen an.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aEdgar Rice Burroughs. 4aGeschichte des 20. Jahrhunderts. 4aGeschichtswissenschaft. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aPopkultur. 4aPopulärkultur. 4aPrimaten. 4aWissenschaft. 4aWissenschaftsgeschichte. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aCultural History.  aHistory of Science.  aHistory of the 20th Century.  aHistory.  aPopular Culture.1 aDenson, Shane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGriem, Julika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHediger, Vinzenz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHochadel, Oliver, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrüger, Gesine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrüger, Gesine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMayer, Ruth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMayer, Ruth, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSommer, Marianne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSommer, Marianne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt0 cprintz978389942882740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839408827?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839408827zOpen Access7042